Our Advisory Process

We believe in the financial planning process. This is the process of identifying goals, gathering and reviewing financial data, and designing and implementing a plan to help you reach your goals. It is a lifelong process. Once the plan is in place, it needs to be monitored, reviewed and updated to meet dynamic circumstances.
 
 





Phase I - Understand


Phase 2 - Design


Phase 3 - Implement


Phase 4 - Manage


Understand

How do you define success?
We will work with you to fully understand where you are now and clarify where you want to go.
What is important to you? What keeps you up at night? How we can help?Design

Our next step is to construct a written financial blueprint:
The Financial Plan

Quantifies your goals
Creates spending priorities
Evaluates risks versus rewards
Connects your income and expenses with your investments
Evolves with you

The Investment Policy Statement

Risk Profiling as a core tenant
Asset allocation targeting based on your risk profilng
Volatility parameters based on current market conditions
Disciplined allocation and rebalancing process
Implement

We then implement solutions to meet your wealth management needs:

Customized action plan for defined outcomes
Coordinate with your other advisors
Tailor solutions
Manage

Wealth management is a lifetime process: 
Where are you relative to your goals?
Has anything changed in your life that will impact your plan?
TMD Wealth Management

Review cash flow and asset/liability needs
Monitor global financial markets
Evaluate managers based on quantitative and qualitative data
Follow a disciplined investment process through risk profiling
Review allocation targets relative to your risk profile
Rebalance your portfolio if applicable
Monitor tax efficiency


 





