Todd Douma, CFP®

This e-mail address is being protected from spambots. You need JavaScript enabled to view it
 





 


President of TMD & Associates
Todd was an honors graduate from Arizona State University and has been in the financial services business since 1994. He was a featured advisor in the 2005 annual report for Raymond James, highlighting his planning and wealth management work on a long-time client of the firm. While at ASU, Todd was a member of the baseball team and went on to play in the New York Mets farm system. He is originally from Oklahoma where he and his wife, Stephanie, met in junior high school. Todd and Stephanie have three children (two of which are twins), enjoy sports, travel, and are actively involved in their church.



Primary Duties at TMD

Provides primary oversight of client portfolios
Facilitates tax, retirement, estate, and other wealth management strategies
Sources alternative investment opportunities for our clients











