Financial Advisor
Jeff is a seasoned advisor with over 30 years of wealth management experience in portfolio, tax, retirement, and estate planning. Jeff has a Master’s in Business Administration, with emphasis in finance and management, from the University of Idaho. Jeff’s thoughts on a number of financial topics have appeared in Sports Illustrated, Time, Reader’s Digest, New Choices, and Newsweek.Prior to becoming a advisor, Jeff played professional tennis and has always been active in sports. He enjoys skiing, golfing, hiking, boating, and just being outdoors. He and his wife, Susan, have four daughters—the youngest is in graduate school at Arizona State.



Primary Duties at TMD

